He is survived by his wife of 54 years, Jean (O’Brien) McCue; his sons Brien (Dorothea) of Shelton and Craig (Fredericka) of Dayton, Ohio, seven grandchildren; Timothy, Kevin, Daniel, Meghan, Brittany, Bailey, Madeline and a sister Joan Boragine.
telegraph and communications. Ed served the Noroton Fire Department as Chief and President and was a volunteer Connecticut State Fire Marshall. He was an active member of the Darien Boat Club and instrumental in its expansion. Ed managed teams in the Darien Little League, Babe Ruth and Sr. Babe Ruth and was also a President of the Darien Little League. Ed received the Darien Old Timers’ Athletic Association Honoree Award in 2003.
